Author: joe@chiang.com.tw
CWLBG stands for Custom Windows Login Background 
Inspired by: HowToGeek's Post http://www.howtogeek.com/112110/how-to-set-a-custom-logon-screen-background-on-windows-7/
Requirements:
1. A JPG file size under 256KB (remember to have the right resolution to your computer monitor)
2. rename the JPG file to backgroundDefault.jpg
3. run CWLBG.exe in Administrator Mode
4. Enter backgroundDefault.jpg folder directory

